text:
Dr. Raulerson has been practicing in Alabama for over 40 years. Today, she reminded us there are many thing we can do to end child poverty. 

But the most important thing we can do is expand Medicaid.

@GovernorKayIvey, are you listening? https://t.co/z0cKK9DF9G

Today marks 10 years since Pres. Obama signed the Affordable Care Act into law. 

The ACA has meant:
✅ Insurance companies can’t charge more for pre-existing conditions;
✅ Women are charged the same as men;
✅ More than 200,000 in AL have gained coverage.

#ProtectOurCare

This closure stands as a stark reminder of what's at stake: access to quality care &amp; hundreds of Alabama jobs.

@SenDougJones and I are working at the federal level to keep our hospitals afloat. 

@GovernorKayIvey &amp; the state legislature need to do their part and expand Medicaid! https://t.co/a7ZFBjjzEL
